## 🐛 Bug Report

Hi team, I noticed a bug when accessing the `dataValidations` through a sheet.
Lib version: 4.4.0
I am applying this to my NestJS code.

## Steps To Reproduce

## My error code:
```typescript
const workbook = new Workbook();
await workbook.xlsx.readFile(templatePath);
const productsSheet = workbook.getWorksheet('products');

productsSheet.dataValidations.add('D2:D9999', {
      type: 'list',
      allowBlank: false,
      showErrorMessage: true,
      formulae: [`product_categories!$B:$B`],
      error: 'Please select any value from dropdown',
 });
// TS Error: Property 'dataValidations' does not exist on type 'Worksheet'.ts(2339)
```
I've checked the `Worksheet` interface that is defined on `index.d.ts`. Actually the `dataValidations` not exist here.

But, when I'm using `as any` for `productsSheet` It work-well 😮
## My update code:
```typescript
const workbook = new Workbook();
await workbook.xlsx.readFile(templatePath);
const productsSheet = workbook.getWorksheet('products');

(productsSheet as any).dataValidations.add('D2:D9999', {
      type: 'list',
      allowBlank: false,
      showErrorMessage: true,
      formulae: [`product_categories!$B:$B`],
      error: 'Please select any value from dropdown',
 });
```

I think the `dataValidations` is available in the JavaScript code but hasn't been added to the TypeScript definition file `index.d.ts`

