I temporarily fixed this issue in my project by using module augmentation. All the methods declared here are implemented, but they weren't correctly typed.

You can add the following in a file like `types/exceljs.d.ts`:

```ts
import 'exceljs';
import { DataValidation } from 'exceljs';

declare module 'exceljs' {
  interface DataValidations {
    add(address: string, validation: DataValidation): void;

    find(address: string): DataValidation | undefined;

    remove(address: string): void;
  }

  interface Worksheet {
    dataValidations: DataValidations;
  }
}
```

